# Code Review Guidelines

> This file configures automated code review (Claude Code /code-review).
> Violations become findings in PR reviews.

## Always check

- New API endpoints have input validation and proper error responses
- Database migrations are backward-compatible (expand-contract pattern)
- Error messages don't leak internal details to users
- No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or credentials
- No secrets or credentials are echoed in example commands, scripts, issue comments, or runbooks
- Authentication/authorization checks on protected endpoints
- SQL queries are parameterized (no string interpolation)
- If the change touches framework/library/API behavior, implementation notes must state `Context7 used: yes/no` and why
- Flag docs-sensitive code that appears guessed from memory instead of checked against current docs
- Current issue acceptance criteria are covered by concrete evidence, not only by summary text
- Rollout changes do not confuse liveness checks with required authenticated smoke
- Warning-only checks are not treated as blocking safeguards
- Docs and runbooks describe the real behavior and remaining manual steps truthfully
- For `BUSINESS_RULES.md` work, newly checked `[x]` items are supported by proof at the same level as the wording claims
- Structural/source-read tests are used only for explicit wiring / existence contracts
- If the slice only proves a weaker contract, the stronger inherited rule stays `[ ]` or is split into a supplemental rule
- Cross-flow claims audit hidden exact-case, raw SQL, and transaction-sensitive paths before marking coverage complete

## Style

<!-- Add project-specific style rules here -->
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals
